that the waiters at Smith &amp;
Wollensky's, they look like--

00:50:25.000 --> 00:50:27.320
they're these big old guys
who look like butchers.

00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:29.420
And in fact, they wear
white butcher's aprons.

00:50:29.420 --> 00:50:30.720
That's what they wear.

00:50:30.720 --> 00:50:33.810
And so we get seated in our
banquet, and out waiter comes over,

00:50:33.810 --> 00:50:36.970
and he says, this six foot tall
guy in a butcher's apron, he says,

00:50:36.970 --> 00:50:38.830
"all right, welcome to
Smith &amp; Wollensky's,

00:50:38.830 --> 00:50:40.130
let's get down to business.

00:50:40.130 --> 00:50:42.830
You know, what are you going to
have tonight to drink, ma'am?

00:50:42.830 --> 00:50:44.130
A martini?

00:50:44.130 --> 00:50:45.430
Good choice.

00:50:45.430 --> 00:50:46.730
For you, sir?

00:50:46.730 --> 00:50:48.030
Another martini, well done.

00:50:48.030 --> 00:50:49.670
Young man, a Coca Cola,
it's on its way.

00:50:49.670 --> 00:50:52.540 position:56%
And what about for the little baby?"

00:50:52.540 --> 00:50:54.440
Now, the second he says this,

00:50:54.440 --> 00:50:56.910
he realizes he's made
a terrible mistake

00:50:56.910 --> 00:50:59.620
from the expression
on my daughter's face.

00:50:59.620 --> 00:51:03.570
So after a moment of
silence, my daughter says

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:05.390
to this six foot tall
guy in a butcher's apron,

00:51:05.390 --> 00:51:10.900
he says, "I am not a baby.

00:51:10.900 --> 00:51:14.670
At the other restaurant,
they call me La Principessa."

00:51:17.260 --> 00:51:18.560
Thank you very much, everybody.

00:51:18.560 --> 00:51:20.770
Thank you for coming out
for the Book Festival.

00:51:20.770 --> 00:51:22.070
Thank you.

